convertFenceToBlackBox(25.10)                    convertFenceToBlackBox(25.10)

Name
       convertFenceToBlackBox - Converts a fence to a blackbox

Syntax
       convertFenceToBlackBox

       [-help]

       {-cell <cellName> | -hinst <hinstName>}

       [-noRebuildTiming]

       [-size { <x><y> }]

       Converts a fence to a blackbox. Use this command before committing par-
       tition.

Parameters
       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies  the name of a module or submodule that should be con-
              verted to a black box.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each convertFenceToBlackBox parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man convertFenceToBlackBox

       -hinst <hinstName>
              Specifies  the  name of the hierarchical instance that should be
              converted to a black box.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -noRebuildTiming
              Skips rebuilding the timing graph and  re-initializing  the  top
              cell information.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -size {<x> <y>}
              Specifies the width and height of the blackbox.

              Default: If you do not specify this parameter, the current fence
              size is taken as the initial size of the blackbox.

              Data_type: point, optional

Example
       The  following  command converts a fence, cp1A to a blackbox with 12,44
       dimensions.

       convertFenceToBlackBox -cell cp1A -size 12 44

